{
  "texts": [
    "A potentially important source of variation in this experiment is the particular subsamples, i.e., the particular realizations of extra, train, and test for a given classification task.",
    "To expose this variation, the experiment procedure is repeated tens of times for each task.",
    "foot_0 For example, for n = 500, and for each of the 25 tasks, 20 (acc extra, acc test, acc base) triples are computed.",
    "Appendix B explains more experiment choices.",
    "5 Results Appendix D.2 visualizes the distributions of acc extra acc base and acc testacc extra."
  ]
}